parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and violent wobbling or shaking of the steering wheel can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel wobbles or shakes violently
especially when driving at high speeds (above 60 mph)
or towing a trailer. The vehicle may drift in the lane
requiring constant steering corrections to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or shift erratically, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the trailer to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: trailer swaying or blocking the roadway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking system can cause the vehicle to roll away, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the electronic systems can cause a loss of critical information, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Electronics on the dash going out
warning lamps or messages not appearing

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to provide timely recall repairs can lead to continued safety risks and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: Parts not available for recall repair
lack of assistance from the manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause driver distraction, loss of control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The sunroof explodes without any apparent reason
with no signs of external damage or impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ease of breaking into the vehicle can result in theft of personal belongings, damage to the vehicle, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Thieves can easily gain access to the vehicle by using a wrench or other tools on the door handle
allowing them to steal valuables or cause damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The severe vibration can cause loss of control, accidents, and premature wear on front-end components, leading to safety risks and increased maintenance costs.
symptoms: making it difficult to read instruments and control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning camera system can cause reduced visibility, increased risk of accidents, and potential harm to pedestrians or objects.
symptoms: The rear camera display becomes dark or black when reversing into a shaded area
making it impossible to see objects or people behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden opening of the tailgate while driving can cause accidents, damage to the vehicle or trailer, and potential harm to occupants or other road users.
symptoms: The tailgate opens unexpectedly while driving
